sluice
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:1. a channel which carries or controls a flow of water. Short form of sluiceway. 2. a gate or valve used to control such a flow. sluice, verb, to send a stream of water out, over or through.
Origin:
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
